00:01:06.444 --> 00:01:08.165
and I am certain that he will find

00:01:08.204 --> 00:01:12.587
a way to share this beautiful scene with

00:01:12.606 --> 00:01:12.727
you.

00:01:14.165 --> 00:01:19.688
Our study today is based upon a mizmor

00:01:19.709 --> 00:01:22.992
that we began just in our last program.

00:01:23.393 --> 00:01:27.816
We had begun to discuss the opening of

00:01:27.897 --> 00:01:30.618
the sixth mizmor, or Psalm of Dode.

00:01:31.058 --> 00:01:33.281
It was interesting because it was a

00:01:33.701 --> 00:01:36.984
celebration of the eighth octave,

00:01:37.325 --> 00:01:39.686
and the fact of the matter is that

00:01:40.373 --> 00:01:45.028
on a piano there are seven keys and

00:01:46.575 --> 00:01:48.677
an eighth octave would be well beyond

00:01:48.897 --> 00:01:52.920
human capacity to both hear, of course,

00:01:53.079 --> 00:01:54.040
also to sing,

00:01:54.641 --> 00:01:56.641
and even beyond instruments to play.

00:01:57.322 --> 00:02:00.584
But it is not beyond where we are

00:02:00.603 --> 00:02:00.884
headed,

00:02:01.665 --> 00:02:04.966
because while God's plan is delineated in

00:02:05.606 --> 00:02:08.389
six plus one equals seven, in other words,

00:02:08.429 --> 00:02:10.590
it took us six thousand years after we

00:02:10.610 --> 00:02:13.372
were booted out of the Gan Eden for

00:02:13.491 --> 00:02:15.752
us to be able to return,

00:02:18.776 --> 00:02:20.396
But principally because, well,

00:02:20.437 --> 00:02:21.777
we didn't measure up in the garden.

00:02:21.798 --> 00:02:23.698
The fact is that neither Adam nor Chawa

00:02:24.497 --> 00:02:25.277
was worth a hoot.

00:02:26.598 --> 00:02:29.158
Neither of them listened to God.

00:02:29.199 --> 00:02:32.060
Neither of them responded appropriately to

00:02:32.219 --> 00:02:32.620
Yahweh.

00:02:33.219 --> 00:02:35.561
Neither of them engaged and contributed

00:02:35.721 --> 00:02:36.681
anything to the garden.

00:02:36.721 --> 00:02:37.980
So they didn't want to work.

00:02:38.281 --> 00:02:40.201
And they certainly showed themselves to be

00:02:40.282 --> 00:02:40.861
unreliable.

00:02:41.581 --> 00:02:42.682
And God knew that it was going to

00:02:42.703 --> 00:02:44.343
take a long time for us to figure

00:02:44.403 --> 00:02:45.003
our way back,

00:02:45.063 --> 00:02:46.705
for us to earn his trust,

00:02:46.746 --> 00:02:49.768
for us to show that we were willing

00:02:49.967 --> 00:02:53.789
to make a contribution and therefore be

00:02:54.890 --> 00:02:57.812
additive as opposed to simply being a

00:02:57.872 --> 00:02:58.373
dependent.

00:02:59.313 --> 00:03:01.294
And as well,

00:03:01.496 --> 00:03:02.856
show that we can get up when we

00:03:02.896 --> 00:03:03.437
fall down.

00:03:04.837 --> 00:03:07.340
Show that we're willing and able to learn.

00:03:07.759 --> 00:03:09.520
And it was all a marvelous story.

00:03:09.580 --> 00:03:10.701
And we've

00:03:12.354 --> 00:03:15.221
