00:38:17.297 --> 00:38:20.398
important truths ever written.

00:38:23.740 --> 00:38:29.405
Your instructions enable me to be correct.

00:38:29.724 --> 00:38:31.347
Your willingness to improve me,

00:38:31.387 --> 00:38:32.567
to teach me, to guide me,

00:38:32.626 --> 00:38:33.228
to train me,

00:38:33.268 --> 00:38:34.909
even to provide discipline for me,

00:38:35.268 --> 00:38:37.351
make me stronger, strengthening me.

00:38:39.655 --> 00:38:41.077
Peel, imperfect, Joseph,

00:38:41.416 --> 00:38:47.961
it's an expression of God's desire to do

00:38:48.001 --> 00:38:49.262
this through dode, imperfect,

00:38:49.282 --> 00:38:50.882
with ongoing implications.

00:38:51.284 --> 00:38:54.846
The peel means that the subject, me, dode,

00:38:56.867 --> 00:38:59.068
has the benefit of what Yahweh is

00:38:59.108 --> 00:39:00.489
achieving through Yatzer.

00:39:00.829 --> 00:39:03.391
And this is so important for people to

00:39:03.791 --> 00:39:04.431
appreciate.

00:39:04.893 --> 00:39:05.132
You see,

00:39:06.811 --> 00:39:07.532
In the garden,

00:39:07.572 --> 00:39:09.713
the reason that Yahweh caused the fall of

00:39:09.753 --> 00:39:11.876
man, and it wasn't Eve,

00:39:12.297 --> 00:39:13.077
Eve didn't even exist.

00:39:13.117 --> 00:39:14.097
It wasn't Chawa,

00:39:14.137 --> 00:39:16.059
the actual name of the woman,

00:39:16.659 --> 00:39:18.221
who caused the fall of man.

00:39:18.601 --> 00:39:20.422
And it wasn't even man's responsibility

00:39:20.463 --> 00:39:21.443
for causing the fall of man.

00:39:21.463 --> 00:39:22.585
Yahweh caused the fall of man,

00:39:22.625 --> 00:39:23.344
made it very clear,

00:39:23.425 --> 00:39:24.286
used the verb in the fall,

00:39:24.967 --> 00:39:27.789
and to describe that he caused the fall

00:39:27.809 --> 00:39:29.389
of man.

00:39:29.751 --> 00:39:33.534
He did so because Adam was not ready.

00:39:34.599 --> 00:39:36.922
He was not ready to be of interest

00:39:36.942 --> 00:39:38.302
to Yahweh,

00:39:38.322 --> 00:39:41.786
was not engaged doing the work that was

00:39:41.846 --> 00:39:45.028
required to make the universe better,

00:39:45.349 --> 00:39:47.590
make the garden better then and the planet

00:39:47.630 --> 00:39:49.231
better and then the universe better.

00:39:49.793 --> 00:39:52.574
He showed no indication he could be

00:39:52.614 --> 00:39:53.036
trusted.

00:39:53.076 --> 00:39:54.797
He was a lousy listener.

00:39:54.836 --> 00:39:56.177
He was not responsive to God.

00:39:56.579 --> 00:39:59.001
And so everything about Dode was just a

00:39:59.081 --> 00:40:01.422
boring and boring

00:40:02.313 --> 00:40:03.733
of no value to Yahweh.

00:40:03.954 --> 00:40:05.376
Might as well be looking at a goldfish

00:40:05.396 --> 00:40:06.195
swimming around in a bowl.

00:40:07.376 --> 00:40:11.740
And so Dode is the opposite of that.

00:40:11.800 --> 00:40:13.242
He's interesting.

00:40:14.702 --> 00:40:17.525
He is a guy that is willing to

00:40:17.545 --> 00:40:19.347
work.

00:40:19.407 --> 00:40:20.807
He wants to be improved.

00:40:21.389 --> 00:40:22.530
He wants to be taught.

00:40:23.389 --> 00:40:26.233
The whole idea of teaching is that

00:40:27.559 --> 00:40:28.561
I don't know about you, but, you know,

00:40:28.681 --> 00:40:30.141
I went to kindergarten,

00:40:30.762 --> 00:40:32.983
then went first grade through sixth grade.

00:40:33.103 --> 00:40:35.085
We call that grammar school back in the

00:40:35.585 --> 00:40:35.925
day.

00:40:36.186 --> 00:40:37.606
And then we had a thing called junior

00:40:37.646 --> 00:40:37.947
high.

00:40:37.987 --> 00:40:39.409
I don't think they call that junior high

00:40:39.449 --> 00:40:39.748
anymore,

00:40:39.849 --> 00:40:41.429
middle school or whatever they call it

00:40:41.469 --> 00:40:41.590
now.

00:40:41.610 --> 00:40:42.510
And then they have upper school.

00:40:42.911 --> 00:40:44.291
We had junior high and high school.

00:40:44.753 --> 00:40:48.235
And then I went to college and then

00:40:48.295 --> 00:40:49.295
I got a Ph.D.

00:40:49.476 --> 00:40:52.838
in writing thirty five dissertations.

00:40:53.639 --> 00:40:54.280
about Yahweh.

00:40:54.639 --> 00:40:58.663
And pushing the threshold of human

00:40:58.702 --> 00:41:00.344
understanding way beyond where it had ever

00:41:00.385 --> 00:41:00.925
been before.

00:41:01.726 --> 00:41:03.947
So in that process,

00:41:04.248 --> 00:41:05.469
when I was in kindergarten,

00:41:05.509 --> 00:41:06.409
first and second grade,

00:41:07.230 --> 00:41:10.253
we did not do calculus.

00:41:10.273 --> 00:41:12.934
There were no lessons on algebra in the

00:41:13.034 --> 00:41:17.438
first grade.

00:41:17.697 --> 00:41:18.798
I did not write...

00:41:22.460 --> 00:41:26.985
essays in uh in kindergarten you know i

00:41:27.045 --> 00:41:30.748
love science but there was no class on

00:41:30.927 --> 00:41:36.351
biology or physics in first grade you know

00:41:36.371 --> 00:41:38.172
you start at the basics yeah you lay

00:41:38.193 --> 00:41:39.795
a foundation if you're going to teach

00:41:39.815 --> 00:41:42.697
someone you have to teach them the basics

00:41:42.757 --> 00:41:45.059
and then you learn from that you start

00:41:45.099 --> 00:41:48.902
with language and and then you build on

00:41:48.961 --> 00:41:50.083
top of of

00:41:51.052 --> 00:41:53.996
layer and layer and layer to the point

00:41:54.317 --> 00:41:57.380
that you can go from well addition and

00:41:57.481 --> 00:42:00.885
subtraction to multiplication and division

00:42:01.686 --> 00:42:04.148
to things like geometry

00:42:05.458 --> 00:42:07.978
and applying those concepts that you've

00:42:08.039 --> 00:42:10.838
learned in geometry and then in algebra

00:42:10.878 --> 00:42:14.699
and then algebra to trigonometry and to

00:42:14.880 --> 00:42:18.521
calculus and then into the concepts of

00:42:18.681 --> 00:42:21.101
probability and statistical analysis.

00:42:21.641 --> 00:42:24.342
And you build this reservoir of

00:42:25.043 --> 00:42:29.985
of knowledge which then properly processed

00:42:30.344 --> 00:42:33.326
can lead to understanding if you're taught

00:42:34.385 --> 00:42:39.947
the discipline of logic and of reason,

00:42:40.728 --> 00:42:41.489
of rhetoric,

00:42:41.989 --> 00:42:45.230
of the skills of debate and what are

00:42:45.289 --> 00:42:48.090
fallacies versus what is evidence.

00:42:49.467 --> 00:42:51.048
provable by evidence and reason.

00:42:51.829 --> 00:42:53.869
And that was my discipline growing up.

00:42:55.971 --> 00:42:59.652
But that was just an academic education.

00:42:59.952 --> 00:43:02.393
That does not prepare anybody for much of

00:43:02.534 --> 00:43:02.934
anything.

00:43:02.954 --> 00:43:04.454
I'm here to tell you, listen,

00:43:04.635 --> 00:43:05.994
I did my thing.

00:43:06.074 --> 00:43:07.635
I'm glad I did my thing.

00:43:07.675 --> 00:43:11.677
But that is not preparation for life.

00:43:11.717 --> 00:43:13.277
You're still, at that point,

00:43:13.358 --> 00:43:14.858
you have paid for your education.

00:43:14.898 --> 00:43:17.800
You have created zip of value.

00:43:18.601 --> 00:43:18.900
Nothing.

00:43:19.735 --> 00:43:21.976
You have not made the world one iota

00:43:22.036 --> 00:43:24.699
better by capitalizing on the education

00:43:24.719 --> 00:43:26.922
that somebody else has provided for you.

00:43:26.963 --> 00:43:28.204
In fact, at that point,

00:43:29.105 --> 00:43:29.925
you're still the parasite.

00:43:32.213 --> 00:43:35.153
until you can pull yourself to the point

00:43:35.653 --> 00:43:36.233
free of that,

00:43:36.293 --> 00:43:37.635
to the point you can then make a

00:43:37.695 --> 00:43:38.275
contribution.

00:43:38.454 --> 00:43:39.875
I started in business.

00:43:40.315 --> 00:43:41.155
I wasn't very good at it.

00:43:41.255 --> 00:43:43.735
I think I've shared that my first year,

00:43:43.755 --> 00:43:45.036
about twenty five cents an hour,

00:43:45.836 --> 00:43:48.018
worked a hundred hours a week,

00:43:48.418 --> 00:43:51.079
which might have gotten to survivable

00:43:51.619 --> 00:43:51.998
income.

00:43:52.298 --> 00:43:53.559
But I was terrible at it.

00:43:53.699 --> 00:43:56.300
I was trying to do the I think

00:43:56.320 --> 00:43:58.721
the hardest job in the world, sell things.

00:43:58.940 --> 00:43:59.041
And

00:44:00.581 --> 00:44:01.641
I was just really crappy at it.

00:44:02.561 --> 00:44:07.063
And so the second year decided, well,

00:44:07.523 --> 00:44:09.083
I'd like to be a success.

00:44:09.463 --> 00:44:11.324
And so I'm going to have to figure

00:44:11.443 --> 00:44:14.065
out a way that I can use my

00:44:14.125 --> 00:44:14.485
skills.

00:44:14.505 --> 00:44:17.746
So my skills were up here primarily.

00:44:18.106 --> 00:44:19.766
I didn't have the great personality.

00:44:19.786 --> 00:44:20.827
I don't guess I've never had a great

00:44:20.867 --> 00:44:23.268
personality, but I was perfect.

00:44:24.146 --> 00:44:26.628
smarter than the average lizard out there.

00:44:27.088 --> 00:44:33.771
And so I use my noggin to conceive

00:44:33.791 --> 00:44:36.092
a way that I could succeed in sales

00:44:36.112 --> 00:44:38.952
without ever having to sell.

00:44:39.012 --> 00:44:42.335
And it was so insightful that if you

00:44:42.795 --> 00:44:46.215
talk to people and find out what they

00:44:46.295 --> 00:44:47.197
want and need,

00:44:48.313 --> 00:44:50.496
and you figure out a way to give

00:44:50.536 --> 00:44:53.137
them what they want to need.

00:44:53.717 --> 00:44:55.378
It means that you have to listen to

00:44:55.418 --> 00:44:55.639
them,

00:44:55.938 --> 00:44:58.201
you have to genuinely care about them,

00:44:58.621 --> 00:45:01.943
you have to then process what they have

00:45:02.023 --> 00:45:02.423
said,

00:45:02.784 --> 00:45:03.985
and then you have to figure out a

00:45:04.025 --> 00:45:07.427
way to determine if the difference between

00:45:07.467 --> 00:45:09.007
what they want, what they need,

00:45:09.307 --> 00:45:10.349
what's good for them,

00:45:10.869 --> 00:45:14.492
and how to deliver it to them in

00:45:14.512 --> 00:45:16.873
the proper way, because if you do that,

00:45:17.833 --> 00:45:19.173
You don't have to sell them anything.

00:45:19.434 --> 00:45:21.094
You're offering them what they already

00:45:21.155 --> 00:45:22.876
want.

00:45:23.195 --> 00:45:28.458
I came up with this approach and made

00:45:28.539 --> 00:45:30.920
millions back in the time when millions

00:45:30.960 --> 00:45:32.641
were actually real money.

00:45:34.322 --> 00:45:36.463
And then parlayed that into company after

00:45:36.523 --> 00:45:37.545
company, and I built things.

00:45:37.644 --> 00:45:38.425
I hired people.

00:45:38.565 --> 00:45:40.927
I conceived new ideas.

00:45:41.067 --> 00:45:42.947
I went after them, approached them,

00:45:42.967 --> 00:45:43.789
and built.

00:45:43.869 --> 00:45:43.949
And

00:45:45.318 --> 00:45:48.019
That's the kind of thing that Yawa is

00:45:48.139 --> 00:45:48.920
looking for.

00:45:49.440 --> 00:45:52.181
And I recognize that in that whole process

00:45:52.242 --> 00:45:55.163
of starting and building companies is that

00:45:55.943 --> 00:45:58.864
every day you're faced with tremendous

00:45:58.905 --> 00:45:59.405
challenges.

00:45:59.425 --> 00:46:01.186
You really have to be devoted to the

00:46:01.226 --> 00:46:01.565
cause.

00:46:01.865 --> 00:46:04.387
You have to invest your own money to

00:46:04.427 --> 00:46:05.108
make payroll.

00:46:05.608 --> 00:46:07.849
You're the last person that gets paid.

00:46:08.509 --> 00:46:10.269
You're responsible for everything.

00:46:10.690 --> 00:46:11.990
And yet you need to be able to

00:46:12.050 --> 00:46:12.610
delegate.

00:46:13.490 --> 00:46:14.311
Otherwise, you can't.

00:46:15.092 --> 00:46:17.753
make a meaningful contribution.

00:46:18.534 --> 00:46:19.876
And then you have to figure out a

00:46:19.896 --> 00:46:23.259
way to share credit and recognize that

00:46:23.278 --> 00:46:24.679
when you share credit and you praise

00:46:24.699 --> 00:46:25.021
people,

00:46:25.420 --> 00:46:27.041
they will very often do what I've seen

00:46:27.141 --> 00:46:28.282
so many people do.

00:46:29.594 --> 00:46:32.115
That means that they will figure out a

00:46:32.135 --> 00:46:35.360
way to turn on you and will use

00:46:35.400 --> 00:46:37.420
what you have said positively about them

00:46:38.503 --> 00:46:39.023
against you.

00:46:39.503 --> 00:46:42.987
And so it is this constant building up

00:46:43.067 --> 00:46:45.568
and then being torn down and making a

00:46:45.648 --> 00:46:47.690
hundred right decisions in a day and

00:46:47.751 --> 00:46:49.932
having the one that wasn't as good as

00:46:49.992 --> 00:46:52.135
it maybe could have been or should have

00:46:52.175 --> 00:46:52.335
been.

00:46:53.777 --> 00:46:56.277
And how you have to recover from that.

00:46:56.338 --> 00:46:57.978
It's this discipline.

00:46:58.500 --> 00:47:01.041
It gives you grit, backbone, stamina,

00:47:01.621 --> 00:47:02.782
resilience.

00:47:03.882 --> 00:47:05.983
It builds a sense of character and

00:47:06.565 --> 00:47:07.344
confidence.

00:47:08.025 --> 00:47:09.806
The only way you know that you can

00:47:09.867 --> 00:47:13.528
prevail when times get tough is to have

00:47:13.568 --> 00:47:15.789
gone through tough times and to have

00:47:15.849 --> 00:47:16.311
prevailed.

00:47:16.791 --> 00:47:18.692
This is what God is looking for.

00:47:19.949 --> 00:47:21.490
for from us.

00:47:21.710 --> 00:47:23.532
It's the thing that Adam did not have.

00:47:23.853 --> 00:47:27.096
It's the thing that Dode had.

00:47:27.215 --> 00:47:29.617
It is what made Dode so special.

00:47:30.278 --> 00:47:31.000
He was a builder.

00:47:33.313 --> 00:47:35.275
And so God recognized,

00:47:35.315 --> 00:47:36.737
and here's Dode speaking to God.

00:47:36.757 --> 00:47:36.996
It says,

00:47:37.036 --> 00:47:39.378
your instructions enable me to be correct.

00:47:39.699 --> 00:47:41.619
Your willingness is to improve me,

00:47:41.981 --> 00:47:45.222
which means that he didn't start perfect.

00:47:45.704 --> 00:47:47.804
He didn't start knowing it all.

00:47:48.085 --> 00:47:51.288
He was taught and he improved.

00:47:51.327 --> 00:47:54.250
He was guided and he was trained.

00:47:54.349 --> 00:47:56.211
God provided discipline,

00:47:56.452 --> 00:48:00.014
which made Dode stronger.

00:48:00.335 --> 00:48:00.554
You know,

00:48:00.952 --> 00:48:02.393
It's a tiny little thing,

00:48:02.434 --> 00:48:03.835
but many of you know,

00:48:04.094 --> 00:48:06.996
because I posted it in the last week,

00:48:07.097 --> 00:48:10.798
I have been troubled by a painful back.

00:48:11.398 --> 00:48:14.041
And never once in this process did I

00:48:14.081 --> 00:48:14.360
say, God,

00:48:14.400 --> 00:48:15.702
could you please make the pain go away

00:48:15.742 --> 00:48:16.641
so I can be productive?

00:48:16.782 --> 00:48:18.322
No.

00:48:18.342 --> 00:48:20.043
What you have to do is to show

00:48:20.543 --> 00:48:24.407
that you're capable of dealing with

00:48:24.527 --> 00:48:25.067
adversity.

00:48:26.353 --> 00:48:28.195
that pain is not something that's going to

00:48:28.255 --> 00:48:30.456
keep you down, that you can do this.

00:48:30.536 --> 00:48:35.460
And it's been difficult to breathe in

00:48:35.500 --> 00:48:37.780
deeply enough to do this program because,

00:48:37.820 --> 00:48:38.061
well,

00:48:38.481 --> 00:48:40.922
you can't speak into a microphone unless

00:48:40.943 --> 00:48:43.344
you have air that goes across your vocal

00:48:43.384 --> 00:48:43.664
cords.

00:48:43.684 --> 00:48:46.445
And when you're sitting down and having

00:48:46.565 --> 00:48:50.168
that kind of compression and this...

00:48:52.014 --> 00:48:56.257
pain that's where the muscles contract

00:48:56.958 --> 00:49:00.541
around it and create that whole it's just

00:49:00.681 --> 00:49:03.605
agonizing it's like knives being in you

00:49:03.644 --> 00:49:06.527
can't deeply enough to project on a

00:49:06.568 --> 00:49:08.690
program like this and I thought that you

00:49:08.710 --> 00:49:09.690
know wincing and pain

00:49:10.010 --> 00:49:12.452
Pain might be inappropriate.

00:49:13.994 --> 00:49:16.416
But it's not like I gave up those

00:49:16.456 --> 00:49:16.715
days.

00:49:16.795 --> 00:49:18.436
I spent almost all of that time.

00:49:18.478 --> 00:49:20.958
I think the entire time I took four

00:49:20.978 --> 00:49:23.822
or five hours off my normal schedule where

00:49:23.902 --> 00:49:25.422
I just had to lay down on a

00:49:25.483 --> 00:49:27.925
hard surface and let everything chill out

00:49:28.565 --> 00:49:30.065
a bit.

00:49:30.106 --> 00:49:32.427
But other than that, I was translating.

00:49:32.487 --> 00:49:35.030
I was working on Bashar Harold Volume

00:49:35.050 --> 00:49:36.471
Four, and here we are back at it.

00:49:36.490 --> 00:49:36.931
I know.

00:49:37.791 --> 00:49:40.253
We may limit our evening program to an

00:49:40.293 --> 00:49:42.755
hour tonight as opposed to two so that

00:49:42.835 --> 00:49:45.257
I'm able to be functional as well

00:49:45.297 --> 00:49:45.697
tomorrow.

00:49:46.057 --> 00:49:48.039
But this is the kind of stuff that

00:49:48.079 --> 00:49:49.740
Yawa is looking for.

00:49:50.380 --> 00:49:53.423
When we had this group of former insiders

00:49:53.463 --> 00:49:56.045
that turned into complete malcontent

00:49:56.525 --> 00:49:59.927
dunderheads and decided that they would

00:50:01.208 --> 00:50:02.829
trash everything that they had once

00:50:02.869 --> 00:50:06.132
supported, the proper...

00:50:07.128 --> 00:50:08.668
Answer is not to say,

00:50:09.010 --> 00:50:10.070
have them just go away.

00:50:10.090 --> 00:50:11.311
They're an irritant.

00:50:11.451 --> 00:50:13.773
No, it's to plow right through,

00:50:14.353 --> 00:50:16.215
to continue the course.

00:50:17.496 --> 00:50:21.079
Expose and condemn as God shows the way

00:50:21.119 --> 00:50:24.681
to do that based upon his prophetic

00:50:24.782 --> 00:50:25.422
instructions.

00:50:25.862 --> 00:50:27.563
But keep right on going.

00:50:29.764 --> 00:50:31.126
Look at Moshe.

00:50:32.047 --> 00:50:33.467
Boy, he had to do it, didn't he?

00:50:34.568 --> 00:50:35.190
Look at Dode.

00:50:35.690 --> 00:50:36.891
He really had to do it.

00:50:37.375 --> 00:50:37.775
Didn't he?

00:50:38.715 --> 00:50:41.458
Both of them encountered inside rebellions

00:50:42.498 --> 00:50:44.239
and painful ones,

00:50:44.581 --> 00:50:47.001
but they had to demonstrate that they

00:50:47.222 --> 00:50:50.005
could endure even through it.

00:50:50.164 --> 00:50:52.887
And this is what God wants of us.

00:50:52.927 --> 00:50:56.989
So your instructions enable me to be

00:50:57.030 --> 00:50:57.469
