01:02:46.755 --> 01:02:47.155
interesting.

01:02:47.255 --> 01:02:47.635
In fact,

01:02:47.974 --> 01:02:49.034
this is one of the things that it's

01:02:49.054 --> 01:02:51.036
just so obvious to me,

01:02:51.615 --> 01:02:53.376
is that if we were perfect,

01:02:53.416 --> 01:02:54.757
let's just say that we want to take

01:02:54.777 --> 01:02:56.197
the religious concept of perfect,

01:02:56.237 --> 01:02:56.978
God's perfect,

01:02:56.998 --> 01:02:58.458
that religious concept of perfect,

01:02:59.018 --> 01:03:00.099
and we were all perfect.

01:03:00.599 --> 01:03:00.780
Well,

01:03:01.139 --> 01:03:02.541
there would be only one paradigm of

01:03:02.561 --> 01:03:02.840
perfect.

01:03:03.715 --> 01:03:04.574
I'd be God.

01:03:04.655 --> 01:03:06.255
And so God's eternity,

01:03:06.315 --> 01:03:07.317
if we're all going to be perfect,

01:03:07.356 --> 01:03:09.438
would be to be surrounded by all little

01:03:09.458 --> 01:03:10.679
me's, many me's.

01:03:11.259 --> 01:03:11.780
Boring.

01:03:12.099 --> 01:03:14.081
Oh, my God, would that be boring?

01:03:14.840 --> 01:03:17.503
It's the things that make us interesting

01:03:17.643 --> 01:03:19.284
are the things like Dode, where God said,

01:03:19.423 --> 01:03:20.605
I like this guy.

01:03:20.945 --> 01:03:22.846
This is my idea of a great guy.

01:03:23.226 --> 01:03:24.706
He was interesting.

01:03:25.306 --> 01:03:29.769
He just had so much personality.

01:03:31.204 --> 01:03:33.925
And so God's not looking for clones.

01:03:34.405 --> 01:03:35.847
He's looking for interesting.

01:03:36.228 --> 01:03:37.389
Eternity is a long time.

01:03:37.668 --> 01:03:40.592
He wants people who he knows he can

01:03:40.632 --> 01:03:42.032
trust, who he can rely upon,

01:03:42.052 --> 01:03:43.474
who he can teach, who will listen,

01:03:43.713 --> 01:03:44.474
who want to grow,

01:03:44.795 --> 01:03:48.038
who he can share eternity with and trust

01:03:48.077 --> 01:03:50.500
that they're going to do the right thing

01:03:50.981 --> 01:03:53.242
when given the opportunity.

01:03:54.583 --> 01:03:55.563
And if we make a mistake,

01:03:55.605 --> 01:03:57.045
we learn from it and go from there.

01:03:58.134 --> 01:03:59.675
This is what God is looking for.

01:03:59.695 --> 01:04:02.737
So this whole religious nonsense about

01:04:02.797 --> 01:04:05.958
perfection is just not understanding the

01:04:05.998 --> 01:04:06.259
word.

01:04:07.300 --> 01:04:09.101
I like it actually as a verb where

01:04:10.302 --> 01:04:14.525
the purpose of the second benefit really

01:04:14.545 --> 01:04:15.184
of the covenant,

01:04:16.786 --> 01:04:18.327
it's a condition of the covenant and then

01:04:18.347 --> 01:04:20.527
a benefit of the covenant is a walk

01:04:20.568 --> 01:04:23.090
to God and allow him to perfect us.

01:04:23.590 --> 01:04:25.972
And when you're dealing with perfection,

01:04:26.132 --> 01:04:27.432
perfect as a verb,

01:04:28.632 --> 01:04:32.273
that I see it as refine, improve,

01:04:32.894 --> 01:04:35.996
knock off some of the rough edges here

01:04:36.016 --> 01:04:36.376
and there,

01:04:37.757 --> 01:04:42.378
allow us to grow and achieve some

01:04:42.418 --> 01:04:43.838
confidence along the way.

01:04:44.099 --> 01:04:45.940
I like the idea of being perfected.

01:04:47.293 --> 01:04:48.695
I just don't like the idea of being

01:04:48.954 --> 01:04:49.275
perfect.

01:04:49.695 --> 01:04:50.677
I don't think God does either.

01:04:51.297 --> 01:04:52.657
I don't think it's realistic and I don't

01:04:52.677 --> 01:04:53.818
think it's even desirable.

01:04:54.518 --> 01:04:57.701
But being perfected absolutely is and

01:04:57.721 --> 01:04:58.961
doubt is the epitome of this.

01:04:59.503 --> 01:05:04.326
So this is a marvelous, marvelous, I mean,

01:05:04.346 --> 01:05:08.648
just tremendous affirmation of everything

01:05:08.688 --> 01:05:10.090
we have come to know and share.

01:05:10.590 --> 01:05:13.492
And here it is so brilliantly presented.

01:05:14.492 --> 01:05:14.632
And

01:05:15.065 --> 01:05:17.306
The opening line of the sixth,

01:05:17.347 --> 01:05:19.628
the number of man, Mizmor,

01:05:20.188 --> 01:05:23.009
of God's beloved son, our Savior,

01:05:23.088 --> 01:05:25.228
our King, the Messiah,

01:05:26.090 --> 01:05:28.971
the man who is not only the exemplar

01:05:29.170 --> 01:05:31.251
of Yisrael and the exemplar of the

01:05:31.291 --> 01:05:31.670
covenant,

01:05:32.211 --> 01:05:33.771
but the man who made it all possible

01:05:33.831 --> 01:05:37.753
for us to share in everything that God

01:05:37.793 --> 01:05:38.273
is offering.

01:05:40.199 --> 01:05:41.460
Thank you for listening.

01:05:41.519 --> 01:05:43.501
I know I talked a lot here and

01:05:43.782 --> 01:05:45.684
talked probably too fast at times.

01:05:46.164 --> 01:05:47.485
There were just so many things I wanted

01:05:47.505 --> 01:05:51.469
to share because this message resonates

01:05:51.489 --> 01:05:51.791
with me.

01:05:52.590 --> 01:05:55.653
It is one of those that I celebrate

01:05:55.673 --> 01:05:58.597
and I'm so thankful for Yahweh for sharing

01:05:58.637 --> 01:05:59.898
it with us.

01:06:01.360 --> 01:06:02.621
Have a wonderful rest of your day.

01:06:02.701 --> 01:06:04.181
Hope to see you this evening as we

01:06:04.202 --> 01:06:05.003
do family hour.

01:06:05.402 --> 01:06:06.423
That will be at,

01:06:07.625 --> 01:06:09.585
I guess that's five o'clock Eastern

01:06:09.806 --> 01:06:10.547
Standard Time,

01:06:10.606 --> 01:06:13.148
six o'clock Atlantic Time here in the

01:06:13.570 --> 01:06:15.371
beautiful Caribbean Sea.

01:06:15.670 --> 01:06:17.833
But it'll be five o'clock Eastern Standard

01:06:17.873 --> 01:06:18.713
Time this evening.

01:06:19.134 --> 01:06:21.335
We will do family hour with the normal

01:06:21.376 --> 01:06:24.237
cast of characters and look forward to

01:06:24.297 --> 01:06:26.360
seeing you there as we continue with our

01:06:26.400 --> 01:06:28.581
series, Return to the Garden.

01:06:29.181 --> 01:06:29.402
Good day.

